<dec f='llvm/clang/include/clang/Sema/Sema.h' l='12111' type='void clang::Sema::checkAllowedCUDAInitializer(clang::VarDecl * VD)'/>
<doc f='llvm/clang/include/clang/Sema/Sema.h' l='12103'>// \brief Checks that initializers of \p Var satisfy CUDA restrictions. In
  // case of error emits appropriate diagnostic and invalidates \p Var.
  //
  // \details CUDA allows only empty constructors as initializers for global
  // variables (see E.2.3.1, CUDA 7.5). The same restriction also applies to all
  // __shared__ variables whether they are local or not (they all are implicitly
  // static in CUDA). One exception is that CUDA allows constant initializers
  // for __constant__ and __device__ variables.</doc>
